President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate John Leonard Badalamenti of Florida as a Judge on the United States District Court for the Middle District of Florida. Badalamenti currently serves as a District Judge on the Florida Second District Court of Appeal and has previously worked as an Assistant Federal Public Defender and an Attorney Advisor for the Federal Bureau of Prisons. He earned his B.A., M.A., and J.D. from the University of Florida. 

The President also intends to nominate Stephen P. McGlynn of Illinois as a Judge on the United States District Court for the Southern District of Illinois. McGlynn currently serves as a Circuit Judge on the Illinois Twentieth Judicial Circuit Court and has previously worked as a Justice on the Illinois Fifth District Appellate Court. He has experience in private practice and has served as a Special Assistant Attorney General of Illinois. McGlynn earned his B.A. from the University of Dayton and his J.D. from St. Louis University School of Law.